  "text": "To assess whether the beneficial effects of nor-NOHA were linked to a decrease in O 2 -. production in the aorta, rings were incubated with the SOD mimetic Tempol and with the NADPH oxidase inhibitor apocynin. Although neither Tempol nor apocynin altered relaxation to Ach in control group ( Figure 5A, B) , they significantly improved vasodilation in untreated AIA rats ( Figure 5C, D) , thus indicating that overproduction of O 2 -. as well as overactivation of NADPH oxidase contribute to endothelial dysfunction in arthritis, as previously demonstrated [CITATION_1] . After treatment with nor-NOHA, the Ach-induced relaxation remained unaffected by both compounds suggesting a normalization of O 2 -. production and NADPH oxidase activity ( Figure 5E , F).",
